      "id": "disa-4",
      "title": "World-in-itself — self-opposed",
      "sourceId": "source-disappearance",
      "sourceFile": "relative/essence/appearance/world/sources/disappearance.txt",
      "lineRange": {
        "start": 40,
        "end": 54
      },
      "description": "World-in-itself in first instance self-identical content, exempt from otherness and change. But content, as complete reflection of world of appearance into itself, or because diversity is difference reflected into itself and absolute, consequently contains negativity as moment. Self-reference as reference to otherness. Thereby becomes self-opposed, self-inverting, essenceless content. Content has retained form of immediate concrete existence. At first ground of world of appearance. But since has opposition in it, equally sublated ground and immediate concrete existence.",
      "keyPoints": [
        "Self-identical content becomes self-opposed",
        "Contains negativity, self-inverting, essenceless",
        "Sublated ground and immediate concrete existence"
      ],
      "orderInSource": 4,
      "globalOrder": 29,
      "sourceText": "Conversely, the world existing in and for itself is\nin the first instance self-identical content,\nexempt from otherness and change;\nbut this content, as complete reflection of\nthe world of appearance into itself,\nor because its diversity is difference\nreflected into itself and absolute,\nconsequently contains negativity as a moment\nand self-reference as reference to otherness;\nit thereby becomes self-opposed, self-inverting, essenceless content.\nFurther, this content of the world existing in and for itself has\nthereby also retained the form of immediate concrete existence.\nFor it is at first the ground of the world of appearance;\nbut since it has opposition in it, it is equally\nsublated ground and immediate concrete existence.",
      "tags": [
        "sublation",
        "reflection",
        "mediation",
        "appearance",
        "world",
        "essence"
      ]
